	"title": "Week 14",
	"content": "<h1 class=\"page-title\">Week 14</h1>\n  \n  <div id=\"todo-date-mount-point\"></div>\n  \n    <p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Overview</span></strong></p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 1\">\n<div class=\"section\" style=\"background-color: rgb(100.000000%, 100.000000%, 100.000000%);\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Stock valuation models, the discounted dividend model (DDM), valuation analysis using multiples, the discounted cash flow model (DCF), fixed income securities and their valuation. Portfolio risk management.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Learning Objectives</span></strong></p>\n<p>Upon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>how to calculate the intrinsic value of a stock using valuation models</li>\n<li>hot to value fixed income securities</li>\n<li>how markets aggregate information into prices</li>\n<li>different types of market information efficiency</li>\n<li>how to measure market reaction to a new informational event (event studies)</li>\n<li>behavioral biases that might affect investor behavior</li>\n<li>behavioral critique to the asset pricing models developed in Lecture 6</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Preparation for class</span></strong></p>\n<p>Mandatory reading:</p>\n<p>Lecture 7: <span class=\"instructure_file_holder link_holder instructure_file_link_holder\"><a id=\"81603454\" class=\"inline_disabled preview_in_overlay\" title=\"Link\" href=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/courses/123249/files/81706672?wrap=1\" target=\"_blank\" data-canvas-previewable=\"true\" data-api-endpoint=\"https://canvas.colorado.edu/api/v1/courses/123249/files/81706672\" data-api-returntype=\"File\">lecture 7.pdf</a><a class=\"file_download_btn\" role=\"button\" download=\"\" style=\"margin-inline-start: 5px; text-decoration: none;\" href=\"https