	"contentText": "Week 14\n  \n  \n  \n    Overview\n\n\n\n\nStock valuation models, the discounted dividend model (DDM), valuation analysis using multiples, the discounted cash flow model (DCF), fixed income securities and their valuation. Portfolio risk management.\n\n\n\n\n \nLearning Objectives\nUpon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:\n\nhow to calculate the intrinsic value of a stock using valuation models\nhot to value fixed income securities\nhow markets aggregate information into prices\ndifferent types of market information efficiency\nhow to measure market reaction to a new informational event (event studies)\nbehavioral biases that might affect investor behavior\nbehavioral critique to the asset pricing models developed in Lecture 6\n\n \nPreparation for class\nMandatory reading:\nLecture 7: lecture 7.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 7.pdf\n \nClass\nClass zoom link: Class logistics\n \nAssignments and Quizzes\nA6\n \nAdditional Resources\nChapter 11, 12, 14, and 18\n \nClass Notes\nNov 18 class recording: \nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/8F1LOHgEUifi439wcDMdXq1boo1uJIQEhOiWwhDL2q_SeZ21hEeY2Feb5sOdWBu-.YDThnrnk1OIYxBHg \n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: 99Ywr^&*\n \nNov 20 class recording: \nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/LitIsB3a_wd_wHpZKweJRlI1d8icyEGwww8H4JSteA1ZMOeFT5yfqIPUy0Y9acT9.EXNvMP64IkbWRcvN \n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: &=x9tFuq\nClass work: DCF Example.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload DCF Example.xlsx\n \n  \n  \n\n",
